commit.message:
Store html content in a data-html attribute. (#66)

* Store html content in a data-html attribute.

The prior approach of using a data URI for the src attribute can
encounter a 2MB limit in Chrome.

* Update geckodriver.

Tests are failing with a WebDriverException.

* Install libgtk-3-0.

The call to 'firefox --version' returns:
  libgtk-3.so.0: cannot open shared object file: No such file or
  directory

* Revert "Update geckodriver."

This reverts commit d63d7fbb1eea0e6abde3fa11eff22e4c740926a9.

* Try another way to install libgtk-3-0

* Add comment with details for dependency.

* Check if this works without apt updating.

One of the tests timed out on the apt update.

* Move 'update' entry higher.

* "update: false" doesn't work as expected.

'apt update' still seemingly runs.
